'''Porvorim''' (Devanagari <U+092A><U+0930><U+0935><U+0930><U+0940>) is the legislative capital of the state of [[Goa]], [[India]]. It the situated on the right bank (north bank) of the [[river Mandovi]]. The administrative capital [[Panaji]] (Panjim) is located on the opposite bank. Porvorim is considered an upmarket residential area as it lies on the prime [[Mumbai]]-[[Goa]] highway NH-17. There are many institutions in Porvorim, most notable is the catering college. Goa Assembly is located here.  

